DISCIPLINARY CASES

2004-2034. Disciplinary Counsel v. Haggins.

On February 9, 2005, respondent filed a motion for extension of time to reply to an order to show cause. S.Ct.Prac.R. XIV(3)(B)(1) prohibits the filing of a request for extension of time to file a response beyond the date set by the court’s order. Accordingly,

IT IS ORDERED by the court, sua sponte, that the motion for extension be, and hereby is, stricken.
